<p>CAMEDIT enables users to edit and make paths that are easily operable and highly efficient for machining. Through the use of CAMEDIT, users can edit entire paths, base paths and path points and also sort the sequence of paths. Furthermore, CAMEDIT enables users to calculate the length beneath the head of blade holder and thus divide paths into machinable sections accordingly. It helps users by creating paths capable of machining the areas that have been left uncut.</p><p><br></p><h2 class="fr-text-bordered">Features</h2><h3>Editing Functions</h3><hr><p>It is possible to utilize users&#39; own expertise of editing paths through the use of a wide variety of capabilities of CAMEDIT, and thus improve machining efficiency.</p><ul><li><strong>Edit of Path</strong><br>Division, Connection, Insertion, Selection, Offset, etc.</li><li><strong>Change of Path Sequence</strong><br>Function that edits machining sequences and directions of paths<br>Alignment, Reverse of direction, Reverse of sequence, Permutation, Alignment for the shortest sequence.</li><li><strong>Edit by the unit of Base Path</strong><br>Function to edit by the unit of base path<br>Connection, Division, Reverse of Direction, Arc</li><li><strong>Edit by the unit of Path Point</strong><br>Function to edit by the unit of Path Point of bath path<br>Extension, Move, Replacement, Deletion, etc.</li></ul><p align="center"><img src="/uelthai/_content_html_editor_upload/images/B8FF026F-5455-B7A4-54E5-91692F94D709.jpeg" width="331" height="194" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p align="center"><br></p><h3>Machinable Segmentation of a Path</h3><hr><p>Paths can be divided into sections that can be machined by the unit of the length beneath the head of a tool holder with blade, provided that the paths have been calculated. Note that the length beneath the tool head varies depending on the combination of holder and blade.</p><p align="center"><img src="/uelthai/_content_html_editor_upload/images/BDAA89FE-6925-31B1-D587-17EE9DF1E520.jpeg" width="452" height="326" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p align="center"><br></p><h3>Edit of Uncut Areas</h3><hr><p>Paths can be edited in order to machine only any uncut areas, by specifying the area and choosing a shape and paths of the previous machining.</p><ul><li>The command enables users to machine a surface evenly, provided that profile lines have been indicated and paths have been created in order to machine any parts left uncut by the previous machining.</li><li>There are two methods for indicating an area subject for processing: &#39;Tool Center&#39; and &#39;Tool Touch Position&#39;.<br>Users can choose either of them in accordance with the purpose of machining.</li></ul><p align="center"><img src="/uelthai/_content_html_editor_upload/images/C8183E89-BCE1-5451-D427-A22470823670.jpeg" width="466" height="255" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p align="center"><br></p><p align="center"><br></p><h3 class="fr-text-bordered">Inquiries</h3><p>If you have any inquiries about our product or would like to request a visit to your place for explanation or demonstration, please use the inquiry form.</p><p style="margin-left: 20px;"><a href="https://singhadevelop-test.com/uelthai/contact"><span style="color: rgb(226, 80, 65);">Contact Us &rarr;</span></a></p><p data-f-id="pbf" style="text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;">Powered by <a href="https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1" title="Froala Editor">Froala Editor</a></p><p data-f-id="pbf" style="text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;">Powered by <a href="https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1" title="Froala Editor">Froala Editor</a></p>